  "response": "If you lack traditional performing talents, here are some options:\n\n1. Comedy/Humor\n- Stand-up comedy\n- Comedic monologue\n- Funny storytelling\n- Improv performance\n\n2. Speaking/Storytelling\n- Personal story/experience\n- Motivational speech\n- TED-style talk\n- Spoken word poetry\n\n3. Interactive/Unique Performances\n- Magic tricks/illusions\n- Simple magic or card tricks\n- Juggling (can be learned quickly)\n- Lip sync performance\n- Mime or physical comedy\n- Unique skill demonstration\n\n4. Low-Skill Performance Types\n- Dramatic reading\n- Character monologue\n- Simple dance routine\n- Deliberately awkward/comedic performance\n- Prop comedy\n- Parody or satire\n\n5. Technology-Assisted\n- Short comedic video\n- Multimedia presentation\n- Slideshow with humorous commentary\n\n6. Group Performance\n- Collaborative skit\n- Group dance/performance where individual skill matters less\n\nTips:\n- Practice beforehand\n- Play to your personality\n- Be confident\n- Focus on entertainment value\n- Embrace humor/self-deprecation if needed\n\nChoose something that feels comfortable and matches your personality.",
